Common.Highlight.Common.Text: TRIPLE NET LEASE TO ASX LISTED TENANT

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE Freestanding Retail Investments & CBRE Victorian Development Sites is pleased to present for your consideration the ‘Preston Toyota Site’, a land-rich intergenerational investment with unrivalled future development scope in Melbourne’s highly sought after inner north.

The property is best described as follows:

+Strategic 1.48ha* premium gateway corner site

+Triple street frontage to High Street (103m*), Regent Street (99m*) and William Street (25m*)

+Established quality improvements comprising 4,700sqm* motor vehicle showrooms, spare parts showroom/store, service centre, carwash and large hardstand area

+Leased to ASX listed Eagers Automotive (ASX:APE) with a market cap of over $4.2Billion.

+Strong net income of $1,082,345 p.a.* plus 3.5% annual increases

+Priority Development Zone (PDZ) promoting high density development (STCA).

+Positioned within Preston’s activity centre, only 250m* to Regent Train Station, 500m* to Woolworths & 600m* to Preston Market.

For Sale Via International Expressions of Interest Closing Thursday 23rd September 2021 at 2:00PM (AEST)

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: BRAND NEW STATE OF THE ART CHILDCARE INVESTMENT WITH NEW 20 YEAR LEASE

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE is pleased to present 597 Gilbert Road, Preston, for lease and available now.

Set on a large site of 233sqm*, this property provides a rare opportunity to lease a blank canvass and turn it into something you can call your own.

The subject property is ideally located on the western side of Gilbert Road, between Union and McNamara Streets, only 9kms* north-east of Melbourne's CBD. It enjoys a unique aspect located directly opposite J S Grey Reserve.

597 Gilbert Road is strategically positioned in proximity to Regent Village and High Street's well-regarded retail strip which incorporates a vast array of national tenants including Woolworths, Aldi and the Preston Market.

Additional features include:
+ Functional single level shop/office of 80sqm*
+ Land area: 233sqm*
+ Huge rear yard/carpark
+ Valuable landholding of 233sqm*
+ Generous rear access
+ Zoned Commercial 1
+ Available now
+ Suit a wide range of uses (STPA)
+ Flexible lease terms and incentives

For further details on this property or your commercial property needs, please contact the marketing agent, Guy Naselli 0413 750 744

*approx.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: MODERN TWO LEVEL OFFICE ON HIGH STREET

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE as the exclusive Agents are pleased to present 86 Bell Street Preston, an exciting large format retail development nearing completion adjacent to Repco, near the corner of Chiffley Drive.

The site shall comprise over 7,200sqm of brand new retail floor space including Baby Bunting, Petbarn and Amart Sports, along with 218 on grade car spaces. Showroom sizes range from 1,000 - 2,120sqm, all with the modern day showroom specifications such as air conditioning, rear loading, lighting and auto-entry doors.

Key Features of this development include;
- Anchored by national brands Baby Bunting, Petbarn and Amart Sports
- Opposite JB Hifi, Super Amart Furniture & Beacon Lighting
- Full multi-directional access from Bell Street
- Ample on grade car parking for customers
- Dominant centre pylon signage to Bell Street

Contact the leasing agent for a detailed leasing prospectus

CBRE Large Format Retail is pleased to present as the exclusive agents Preston Northland Homemaker Centre.

The Northland Homemaker Centre is recognised as one of Melbourne’s more desirable centres and the dominant centre for the northern suburbs. The centre features an abundance of national brands, ample on grade car parking and a strategic position immediately opposite the Super Regional Northland Shopping Centre.

- Join JB Hi-Fi, Freedom Furniture, The Good Guys, Fantastic Furniture plus a long list of other national brands.
- Strategic location opposite Northland Shopping Centre in a densely populated catchment experiencing high volumes of gentrification.
- Brand the exterior of the showroom in corporate colours
- Approximately 1.5million people within a 20 minute drive time
- Existing fit out including suspended ceiling, recessed lighting and rear loading.

The 7,000sqm centre is strategically positioned in this dominant retail hub immediately adjacent to Bunnings Warehouse, Masters Home Improvement Centre and the Super Regional Northland Shopping Centre. Available immediately, be sure not to miss this prime corner of a prime homemaker centre!
